<TITLE> Mutiny-hit SSC examinees to take maths on Mar 19 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 5 (bdnews24.com) - The SSC examinees affected by the BDR mutiny, who were unable to take their mathematics exam on Feb 25, will be able to sit for it on March 19, said a government handout Thursday. Their remaining SSC exams will also be rescheduled on special consideration, it said. The affected examinees will have to notify the Controller of Examinations directly or via their headmasters by March 10 for exams on March 1 and afterwards. The education ministry decided on Feb 28 to make special arrangements for the mutiny-hit SSC examinees
